definitions.definition: An item of clerical clothing : a long, sheath -like, close-fitting, ankle-length robe worn by clergy members of some Christian denominations.
A military cloak or long coat worn by soldiers or horsemen in the 16th and 17th centuries.
A coarse, loose cloak or gown , worn by women, sailors, shepherds, countryfolk etc.

main_definition: An item of clerical clothing : a long, sheath -like, close-fitting, ankle-length robe worn by clergy members of some Christian denominations. [from 17th c.]
